<refentry xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5.0-subset Scilab" xml:id="standard_inputs">
  <refnamediv>
    <refname>standard_inputs</refname>
    <refpurpose>Get the position of the input ports of a block in Xcos editor</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <title>Calling Sequence</title>
    <synopsis>[x,y,typ] = standard_inputs(block)
    </synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsection id="Module_standard_inputs">
    <title>Module</title>
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          <link linkend="xcos">xcos</link>
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
  </refsection>
  <refsection id="Description_standard_inputs">
    <title>Description</title>
    <para>
      This Scilab function is used to get the position (x,y) of each input port of an Xcos block.
      The returned typ variable is used to make the difference between standard input ports and clock input ports. 
      The typ variable can take the following values: 1 if this is a standard input port; -1 if this is a clock input port
    </para>
    <para>
    </para>
    <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[ 
loadXcosLibs();
o = CSCOPE("define");
[x,y,typ] = standard_inputs(o)
 ]]></programlisting>
  </refsection>
  <refsection id="Parameters_standard_inputs">
    <title>Arguments</title>
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          <emphasis role="bold">block :</emphasis> xcos block
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          <emphasis role="bold">x :</emphasis> x position of the port. When multiple ports are described, x is a float vector of x positions.
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          <emphasis role="bold">y :</emphasis> y position of the port. When multiple ports are described, y is a float vector of y positions.
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          <emphasis role="bold">typ :</emphasis> determine the type of ports. It can take the following values : 1 if this is a standard port; -1 if this is a clock port. When multiple ports are described, typ is a vector.
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
  </refsection>
</refentry>
